(132, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://make.wordpress.org/core/2013/07/28/potential-roadmap-for-taxonomy-meta-and-post-relationships/'' title=''A non-trivial undertaking. I’m always a bit wary of “clever” solutions and long term maintainability, but in this case the benefit of dropping a table makes it worthwhile. # [&hellip;]''>Alex King: Potential roadmap for taxonomy meta and post relationships</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/07/27/matt-mullenweg-qa-from-the-state-of-the-word-2013/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Matt Mullenweg: Q&amp;A from the State of the Word 2013</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/07/27/matt-mullenweg-state-of-the-word-2013/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Matt Mullenweg: State of the Word 2013</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/N0fjkfosQ0s/the-daily-plugin-launchkey-user-languages-buy-him-a-beer'' title=''It’s once again time to check out the newest and most recently updated plugins in the WordPress Plugin Repository. Today we have five additions that are worth taking a closer look at. But before you install these on a live site, make sure that you properly test them on a secondary staging site first. That way you know the plugin is an ideal match for you and [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: The Daily Plugin: Launchkey, User Languages, Buy Him A Beer</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://2013.sf.wordcamp.org/session/teaming-up-from-freelance-to-wordpress-agency/'' title=''I’ll be paneling at WordCamp SF on Saturday at 3:30pm along with Jake Goldman of 10up, Shane Pearlman of Modern Tribe and Brad Williams of Web Dev Studios. Each of us have taken different paths and approaches to build our teams, so the contrast in perspectives should make for a good discussion. We will be grilled by the one and only Matt Mullenweg, do